spirit:busInterface.spirit:name: S_AXI
spirit:busInterface.spirit:description: s_axi bus interface that supports both AXI4 and AXI4Lite

spirit:field.spirit:name: REGADDR
spirit:field.spirit:description: PHY register address

spirit:field.spirit:name: PHYADDR
spirit:field.spirit:description: PHY device address

spirit:field.spirit:name: OP
spirit:field.spirit:description: Operation Access Type 0 - Write Access 1 - Read Access

spirit:field.spirit:name: MDIO_WDATA
spirit:field.spirit:description: MDIO write data to be written to PHY register

spirit:field.spirit:name: MDIO_RDATA
spirit:field.spirit:description: MDIO read data from the PHY register

spirit:field.spirit:name: MDIO_Status
spirit:field.spirit:description: MDIO status bit 0 - MDIO transfer is complete and core is ready to accept a new MDIO request 1 - MDIO transfer is in progress. Setting this bit initiates an MDIO transaction. When the MDIO transaction is complete, the AXI Ethernet Lite MAC core clears this bit PHY register address

spirit:field.spirit:name: MDIO_Enable
spirit:field.spirit:description: MDIO enable bit 0 - Disable MDIO interface 1 - Enable MDIO interface

spirit:register.spirit:name: TX_Ping_Length
spirit:register.spirit:description: Transmit length register for ping buffer

spirit:field.spirit:name: TX_Ping_Length_LSB
spirit:field.spirit:description: The lower 8 bits of the frame length

spirit:field.spirit:name: TX_Ping_Length_MSB
spirit:field.spirit:description: The higher 8 bits of the frame length

spirit:field.spirit:name: GIE
spirit:field.spirit:description: Global Interrupt Enable bit

spirit:register.spirit:name: TX_Ping_Control
spirit:register.spirit:description: Transmit control register for ping buffer

spirit:field.spirit:name: Status
spirit:field.spirit:description: Transmit ping buffer status indicator 0 - Transmit ping buffer is ready to accept new frame 1 - Frame transfer is in progress. Setting this bit initiates transmit transaction. When transmit is complete, the AXI Ethernet Lite MAC core clears this bit.

spirit:field.spirit:name: Program
spirit:field.spirit:description: AXI Ethernet Lite MAC address program bit. Setting this bit and status bit configures the new Ethernet MAC address for the core.

spirit:field.spirit:name: Interrupt_Enable
spirit:field.spirit:description: Transmit Interrupt Enable bit 0 - Disable transmit interrupt 1 - Enable transmit interrupt

spirit:field.spirit:name: Loopback
spirit:field.spirit:description: Internal loopback enable bit 0 - No internal loopback 1 - Internal loopback enable

spirit:register.spirit:name: TX_Pong_Length
spirit:register.spirit:description: Transmit length register for pong buffer

spirit:field.spirit:name: TX_Pong_Length_LSB
spirit:field.spirit:description: The lower 8 bits of the frame length

spirit:field.spirit:name: TX_Pong_Length_MSB
spirit:field.spirit:description: The higher 8 bits of the frame length

spirit:register.spirit:name: TX_Pong_Control
spirit:register.spirit:description: Transmit control register for pong buffer

spirit:field.spirit:name: Status
spirit:field.spirit:description: Transmit pong buffer status indicator 0 - Transmit pong buffer is ready to accept new frame 1 - Frame transfer is in progress. Setting this bit initiates transmit transaction. When transmit is complete, the AXI Ethernet Lite MAC core clears this bit.

spirit:field.spirit:name: Program
spirit:field.spirit:description: AXI Ethernet Lite MAC address program bit. Setting this bit and status bit configures the new Ethernet MAC address for the core.

spirit:register.spirit:name: RX_Ping_Control
spirit:register.spirit:description: Receive control register for ping buffer

spirit:field.spirit:name: Status
spirit:field.spirit:description: Receive status indicator 0 - Receive ping buffer is empty. AXI Ethernet Lite MAC can accept new valid packet. 1 - Indicates presence of receive packet ready for software processing. When the software reads the packet from the receive ping buffer, the software must clear this bit.

spirit:field.spirit:name: Interrupt_Enable
spirit:field.spirit:description: Receive Interrupt Enable bit 0 - Disable receive interrupt 1 - Enable receive interrupt

spirit:register.spirit:name: RX_Pong_Control
spirit:register.spirit:description: Receive control register for pong buffer

spirit:field.spirit:name: Status
spirit:field.spirit:description: Receive status indicator 0 - Receive pong buffer is empty. AXI Ethernet Lite MAC can accept new available valid packet. 1 - Indicates presence of receive packet ready for software processing. When the software reads the packet from the receive pong buffer, the software must clear this bit

spirit:modelParameter.spirit:name: C_INCLUDE_GLOBAL_BUFFERS
spirit:modelParameter.spirit:displayName: Include global buffers for PHY clocks

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_RX_PING_PONG
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Set this parameter to include the no. of Receive Buffers.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_TX_PING_PONG
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Set this parameter to include the no. of Transmit Buffers.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_INCLUDE_GLOBAL_BUFFERS
spirit:parameter.spirit:displayName: Enable Global Buffers for PHY Clocks
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Enabling this parameter includes global buffers for PHY clocks which can be used to minimize the clock skew on the PHY clocks.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_INCLUDE_INTERNAL_LOOPBACK
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Enabling this parameter includes BUFG for PHY clock switching when loopback is enabled.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_INCLUDE_MDIO
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Including the MDIO interface allows PHY register access from AXI Ethernet Lite MAC core.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_S_AXI_PROTOCOL
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter decides the AXI interface of the core.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_DUPLEX
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Set this parameter for choosing Full Duplex or Half Duplex mode.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: AXI_ACLK_FREQ_MHZ
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: The AXI4 clock frequency must be greater than or equal to 100 MHz for 100 Mb/s Ethernet operation and greater than or equal to 10 MHz for 10 Mb/s Ethernet operation.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: Enable_Constraints
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Enabling this parameter includes I/O constraints on the PHY ports through TCL. If internal PHY is used, this parameter has to be disabled.
